Text.Value: Clearing that rubble will be no easy feat. Any ideas?
Let me guess - Brithvar and Kur. They've been a thorn in my arse since Nere hired us.
That so? Set it near the rubble and ignite it. That'll blow the drow out.
Bare feet, I see. I nabbed these boots from a runaway gnome - yours, perhaps?

EditorData.logicalname: Have boots, but didn't talk to Lone Duergar. Know Thulla run away from duergar.

Text.Value: I heard a gnome fled the dig. What happened?
Moonrise? There's a lot resting on what we find in that place. It had better deliver.

EditorData.NodeContext: Discreet reference to Nere, whose head we're to collect as a bounty.

Text.Value: Never thought I'd see these back. Nasty sneak gave even Gekh the slip.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Thrinn] gestures backwards towards a [Gnome], who comes scurrying towards [Thrinn]. She then gestures towards her feet. The [Gnome] crawls down and puts the boots on [Thrinn], who shifts her weight as offscreen she is put into her boots. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Thrinn accepts boots. No need to show in cinematic - since she is already holding the cane.

Text.Value: I was told to report to you. Gekh Coal is dead.

EditorData.logicalname: Came by saying Gekh was dead

Text.Value: Place is older than bonedust. Previous tenants left a trap - dropped a shit-tonne of metal once we'd dug a ways in.
Forget the boots. I'm here to check on the dig.
Bare feet, I see. I nabbed these boots from a runaway gnome - yours, perhaps?

EditorData.logicalname: Have boots, but didn't talk to Lone Duergar. Know Thulla run away from duergar.

Text.Value: I had a chat with Nere, and you're in big trouble.
Poorly, obviously. Tunnel collapsed on a True Soul. Absolute's going to eat my liver.
Yes, True Soul?
Nere can handle himself. Reason I joined - I know which way the lava flows.
They don't get paid soon, I'll have a riot on my hands.
Then find the thievin' bugger and get them back.
Move. I don't have time for you.
Move, hoon. I don't have time for drugnin' outsiders.

EditorData.NodeContext: 'hoon' means outside, pronounced as it is spelledr. DRUG-nin (means fucking, as an expletive)

Text.Value: Didn't realise we were flirting - just be warned, I hear I taste bitter.
A True Soul, eh? Useless rakkah of a lookout could've told me.
You think your boss will be happy you attacked a True Soul?

EditorData.logicalname: LOGIC NODE - Halsin Talked of Moonrise

Text.Value: My arm's near dead from the lashing. The prick-squeaks are digging as fast as I can make them!
I noticed an orb floating about. What's it doing?

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Tagged as not REALLY_GNOME to prevent multiple similar options

Text.Value: Leave.
Moonrise. We're getting close to the lion's den - and plenty of questions I have for the lion, too.
Give her the gnome's boots.
Not a one - unless you count tacking aboleth fangs to my whipping cane.
Thought you would. True Souls don't abandon their own.
You the one Greymon mentioned? Heard you killed that thievin' gnome. Where's my boots?
Hells. How sick must a soul be to take slaves, let alone lash them?
Get Nere out and you'll have the Absolute's blessing, no doubting that.
You got those boots? Or something else eatin' at you?
How did Nere get trapped?
You spoke with him? Then you connected. You are a True Soul.
Charming. Hell is truly where we make it.
Here, then - his bounty's yours.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* CINE animation to show [Thrinn] leaning forward to give reward. Could try CINE_ProduceInventory_StandR_03. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Reward given. Could show Thrinn leaning forward to player, but no need for cinematic to show the reward being given otherwise.
EditorData.NodeContext: neutral - she might know we're a True Soul or not, so shouldn't be jarringly aggressive or sycophantic. Just closing one matter and moving onto the next.

Text.Value: I'd like to know more about Moonrise.
Who is operating the scrying eye I've seen floating around?
Dead? Drugnin' Gekh - figured I could count on him. Lesson damn well learned.
Entrance to an ancient temple. General's orders, Nere said. Must contain somethin' important.
Now move. I've got no time for -
Nere isn't happy. These gnomes better start digging faster.
Prepare for a fight.
*The parasite stirs, but it's a mere tickle. You hear no thoughts or memories, just an echo of scars that never healed.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* Can use an appropriate CINE_MindMeld_Level_ for the [Player] mindmelding with [Thrinn]. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind-meld between Thrinn and the player

Text.Value: Glad you're here to take responsibility. Tunnel's collapsed, trapped True Soul Nere.

EditorData.NodeContext: drugning is an expletive (like fucking), pronounced DRUG-ning (g is silent for duergar)

Text.Value: Nere spoke to me; our minds connected. And he's not happy.
That's Moonrise, keeping tabs. Nere says they've scryers watching the Absolute's followers for trouble, non-stop.
That's not what the lookout told me. Hand 'em over, or I'll take them off your corpse.
On the double ya pricks, before I carve my name into your arses.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *DUPE*[Thrinn] turns, and threathens the gnomes with her cane. Could use a construction anim (Torso turn of DFLT_CINE_Point_LeftToRear_01 perhaps) to empahsise the turn and action further than it is in the V.O animation. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed  to gnomes digging at the cave-in.

Text.Value: What is it with these people and heads? Let's get Nere's and get out.
Brithvar's dead. I - I proved myself. No way Nere can doubt me now.
I've got some explosive powder. That should do the trick.
It is Nere's head that concerns us.

EditorData.NodeContext: Plainly stated, as if it's obvious. We're here to kill Nere, but Thrinn thinks we're here to save him. The player likely wants to keep it secret, but Lae'zel doesn't get subterfuge.

Text.Value: Let's all keep our heads, eh? You, us... Nere.

EditorData.NodeContext: Forced levity - a side-glance at the player referencing that we're actually here to kill Nere, not save him.

Text.Value: A slave stole them. I'm searching for the culprit.
Yes, True Soul?
Sounds like you have a tough job ahead of you. Better hurry.
Give her the gnome's boots.
*Ancestral memories haunt your mind. Your people were once mind flayer slaves, and still carry the remnants of their illithid powers.*

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE* Can use an appropriate CINE_MindMeld_Level_ for the [Player] mindmelding with [Thrinn]. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Mind-meld between Thrinn and the player

Text.Value: Leave.
Is this how you welcome a True Soul?
Moonrise? We're closing in on the Towers. And the curse...

EditorData.NodeContext: Forced levity - a side-glance at the player referencing that we're actually here to kill Nere, not save him.

Text.Value: Drugnin' shitshow, it was. Couple of pricklets figured they'd blow us clear to the topland.
I'll take care of it.
I'm splittin' for Moonrise Towers. It's time the General made me a True Soul.
Give her the gnome's boots.
How is the dig going?
Ignore dumb and dumber. They'd jump down a well if they though there was gold at the bottom.
Then go get them.

EditorData.NodeContext: slow down the speech a little, as if she's talking to someone stupid.

Text.Value: I don't have them.
What now?
I don't have them.

EditorData.stateContext: Thrinn holds a cane used for whipping through the scene.

Text.Value: Watch your tone. I bite.
An escort to Moonrise, huh? Can't be too far off, then.
The Towers must be close. And finding Moonrise means finding answers.
Get lost.
Forget them? What drugnin' game are you -
Faster!

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Thrinn] turns, and threathens the gnomes with her cane. Could use a construction anim (Torso turn of DFLT_CINE_Point_LeftToRear_01 perhaps) to empahsise the turn and action further than it is in the V.O animation. <LoganP>

Text.Value: I've got some explosive powder. That might clear the debris.
You better make time for a True Soul.
A few of your clanmates are plotting to kill Nere.

EditorData.logicalname: Duergar told their plan, not dead

Text.Value: Not the head we'd like to see roll, unfortunately...

EditorData.NodeContext: Discreet reference to Nere, whose head we're to collect as a bounty.

Text.Value: The famous Nere - subject of the myconids' ire, no?
Moonrise? We're nearing the Towers. We're nearing answers.

EditorData.NodeContext: Plainly stated, as if it's obvious. We're here to kill Nere, but Thrinn thinks we're here to save him. The player likely wants to keep it secret, but Lae'zel doesn't get subterfuge.

Text.Value: You don't know about the seat of the Absolute? No doubt you'll see it for yourself soon enough.

EditorData.NodeContext: Thrinn is a bit surprised but shrugs it off

Text.Value: No need for that - Nere's is the only head that matters to us.
Go on already, ignite the powder!
Nere caught 'em scheming. Handed a few to an escort - dragged to Moonrise, is my guess.
Can't wait to pay these bastards back, lick for lick. Just say the word.
Hmph. Not the most sophisticated way of getting what you want from someone, is it?
Heat up some rocks. Let's see how the little pricks do when we strap fire to their legs.
I need labour, not bloody advice. If I don't get this rubble clear and free the True Soul, it'll be my head.
Give her the gnome's boots.
You gonna just leave him in there to choke? Shit.
What are you hoping to find at this dig?
Crafty little shits, these ones. You need a stiff cane to keep 'em in line.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Thrinn] shifts her weight as the [Gnome] puts the boots on her. Cut to show [Gnome] finishing putting her boots on. They give them a quick dust and knocking some dirt off. <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Thrinn puts on the boots, then stands.
EditorData.SFXTags: Thrinn equipping the boots you gave her

Text.Value: He got me to recruit nonbelievers. But not everyone's seein' the Absolute's truth.
Scrying eye. Nere says the Absolute's scryers see through 'em. Watching. Judging.
Judging by the sorry state of your dig, you should.
Go on already, ignite the powder!
I'm no fool, jargh. Hand 'em over, or I'll bring the Absolute's fury.
But one pudge got ballsy, set off a blast and skittered away in the ruckus. And we still haven't found her.
He's stuck in there with poisoned geysers. We don't get him out soon, it's both our heads.

EditorData.AnimationTags: *REUSE*. 1) Either new custom anim of [Gnomes] digging with hands, or use a Cinematic-Modified version of GNO_M_Rig_DFLT_UTIL_Mine_01. 2) [Thrinn] points to the cave-in - could use DFLT_CINE_PointLeft_LHand_StandL  <LoganP>
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: When Nere mentions Nere is stuck, show cave-in with gnomes digging in front of it.

Synopsis: The duergar sergeant responsible for the camp while Nere is trapped. She's yelling at the gnomes and is considerably pissed off. After realising you are a True Soul, she asks you to help free Nere from the cave-in, and you can refuse or accept. You might turn in her missing boots if you have found them You can also ask about the gnome that escaped and the scrying eye.
